<TITLE> PM releases commemorative stamp, envelope </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 16 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has released a postage stamp and envelope on Friday commemorating the World Food Day. The event took place at the premier's residence where Ad Spijkers, country representative of UN's Food and Agriculture Organisation, agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury and telecommunications minister Raziuddin Ahmed Razu were also present. The day is being observed Friday around the globe with the theme of 'Achieving Food Security in Times of Crisis.' On Thursday, president Zillur Rahman stressed proper measures to ensure food security in a changing climate. In his message on Thursday, he said, "I believe sufficient research and adequate technological innovation and usage can play an important role to produce more food." The prime minister in her message said that agriculture was the most affected and vulnerable sector due to climate change. "It is absolutely needed to ensure food security by fighting the situation." She said that the country had achieved self-sufficiency during the previous Awami League government in 1996-2001. "But the succeeding government could not continue with the success." The incumbent government is committed to guarantee food security for all, added Hasina. Quite a few numbers of programmes were held across the country to mark the day. Matia inaugurated the day's events through a rally that started from Khamar Bari in Dhaka, participated among others by agriculturists, scientists, officials and members of the public. Hundreds of school children joined the rally with colourful banners and festoons. The programme was supported by Telefood, a FAO project for eradicating hunger, bdnews24.com and Channel i. A seminar in observance of the day was also held at Bangladesh Agricultural Research Council, attended by Matia and food and disaster management minister Abdur Razzaque. Minister of fisheries and livestock Abdul Latif Biswas also participated in the seminar where Ad Spijkers was the guest of honour. A children's painting competition was arrenaged at 3pm at Bangladesh Shishu Academy. A three-day fair on 'Agriculture and Food' was inaugurated at the Krishibid Institution premises at 12pm. A similar fair was being held at Depasai village in Somobhat union under Dhamrai upazila. Channel-i telecast the programme live. The district and upazila administrations around the country observed the day through holding discussion meetings and rallies. bdn
